This script has been tested on CentOS 7 with GNome 3

For installation, do the following:

1. Install 'ykinfo' executable - Package 'ykpers' on CentOS 7

Now, go on by installing  the script:

2. Put '99-yubikey-screen-lock.rules' to /etc/udev/rules.d/
3. Do a 'sudo udevadm control --reload-rules'
4. Edit 'yubikeys' to include your user and the serial of your yubikey
5. Put 'yubikeys' to /etc/sysconfig/
6. Put 'yubikey-screen-lock' to /usr/local/bin/ and make it executable


Now, go ahead with testing the stuff by plugging in/out you yubikey
